# Admin Panel Development Guidelines

## Admin Architecture
The admin panel is located in [src/app/admin/](mdc:src/app/admin/) with the following structure:

### Core Components
- Layout: [src/app/admin/layout.jsx](mdc:src/app/admin/layout.jsx)
- Main page: [src/app/admin/page.jsx](mdc:src/app/admin/page.jsx)
- Sidebar: [src/components/admin/Sidebar.jsx](mdc:src/components/admin/Sidebar.jsx)

### Admin Sections
- Products: [src/app/admin/products/](mdc:src/app/admin/products/)
- Applications: [src/app/admin/applications/](mdc:src/app/admin/applications/)
- Accessories: [src/app/admin/accessories/](mdc:src/app/admin/accessories/)

## Data Management Patterns

### Table Components
Follow the pattern established in [src/app/admin/products/Table.jsx](mdc:src/app/admin/products/Table.jsx):

```jsx
const AdminTable = ({ data, columns, actions }) => {
  return (
    <div className="admin-table">
      <table>
        <thead>
          {/* Column headers */}
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {data.map(item => (
            <tr key={item.id}>
              {/* Table cells */}
              <td className="actions">
                {/* Edit, Delete, View actions */}
              </td>
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  );
};
```

### API Integration
Admin pages should integrate with backend APIs from [ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/](mdc:ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/):

```jsx
// Products API: ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/products.js
// Accessories API: ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/accesories.js
// Applications API: ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/application.js

const fetchData = async () => {
  try {
    const response = await fetch('/api/products');
    const data = await response.json();
    // Handle data
  } catch (error) {
    // Handle error
  }
};
```

## Authentication & Security
- Implement authentication checks for all admin routes
- Use middleware to protect admin endpoints
- Follow authentication patterns from [ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/auth.js](mdc:ddgro-nowy-backend/routes/api/auth.js)

## Navigation & Layout
- Use consistent sidebar navigation from [src/components/admin/Sidebar.jsx](mdc:src/components/admin/Sidebar.jsx)
- Maintain breadcrumb navigation for deep admin sections
- Implement responsive admin layouts

## CRUD Operations
Standard patterns for Create, Read, Update, Delete operations:
- List views with pagination and search
- Modal or page-based forms for create/edit
- Confirmation dialogs for delete operations
- Proper error handling and user feedback

## Data Validation
- Client-side validation for forms
- Server-side validation in API endpoints
- Consistent error messaging
- Form state management with proper loading states
